icy has remained in the hands of the party leadership. The study also suggests that the party grassroots are interested in the EU, but that interest rarely translates into influence. As regards the selection of EU specialists, this book highlights that the parties’ processes are highly political, often informal, and in some cases, undemocratic.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aDemocracyzEuropean Union countries. 0aSocialismzEuropean Union countries. 4aPolitical Studies 2019. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Comparative Politics.2bisacsh  aCentre-left parties.  aEU Specialists.  aEuropean policy.  aGrassroots members.  aIntra-party democracy.  aLabour Party.  aParti Socialiste.  aParty of European Socialists.  aSocial Democracy.  aSozialdemokratische Partei Deutschlands.1 aHertner, Isabelle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2018 eBook-Packagez978311128277040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152612034240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526120342423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526120342/original  a978-3-11-128277-0  Manchester University Press 2018 eBook-Packageb2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles